Food at Ella's was delicious! We ordered 4 different personal pizzas - meatball, margherita, Ella's cheese with smoked bacon, and the Genovese - and a burger. Everything was delicious. The bacon on the cheese pizza was cooked perfectly, as was the burger (we ordered it medium & it was lightly pink & really juicy). Finally, we ordered a gluten-free Genovese (their gluten-free menu was what drew us to Ella's in the first place) and it was delicious. First, I must share that the food was delicious and very fresh.  The portions and toppings were generous.  We chose this restaurant specifically because they offer a gluten free pizza option, and it was delicious as well.  It is also important to know that we did not have to wait long for our food to be served. The problem we had surrounded the customer service.  We were a party of 6 and were charged an automatic 20% gratuity.  First, I've worked in the restaurant industry, and mandatory gratuity usually does not start until you are a party of 8.  Secondly, the assumption was made that we had a service worthy of 20% gratuity, we did not.  To further frustrate the experience, four different credit cards were declined upon the server trying to run our cards in the machine.  I can ASSURE you we had plenty of money in our accounts and were having no problems using any of our cards in DC.  We then had to wait for my husband to run out and get cash from a machine.  The server admitted that there was a problem with their machine and that the manager would come to our table to discuss the matter, he/she did not.

I walked in with a group of 7, with 4 of them being kids. Food was served pretty quickly. But service was lacking, once we received the food, nobody came and checked on us.  Had to get up and seek attention just to get more water. We felt since gratuity was included because the size of our group that we were just sat in the back and was an inconveience. Definitely wouldn't go back. Poor experience.
